  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures: it analyzes patterns in where failures occur (e.g., which coverage criteria expose more errors), links failure discovery to model internals (neuron-based coverage criteria such as KMNC, NBC, SNAC, TKNC), and empirically connects testing strategy choices (seed selection, mutation validity) to reduced/increased error discovery. It also empirically relates failures introduced by quantization to corner-region coverage (NBC/SNAC) and to model size/quantization ratio. However, the paper does not trace discovered failures back to deeper root causes such as corrupted or biased training data, spurious features learned from the dataset, or overfitting; the explanations remain at the level of model-internal activation/coverage patterns and statistical/behavioral correlations rather than definitive causal attributions to training-data or learning-process vulnerabilities. Thus the contribution is diagnostic but partial (model-internal and pattern-based), matching the Medium level.",
